UID:4f2ad1petsmbfs5up1c2dj0u9o@google.com
CREATED:20210405T135741Z
DESCRIPTION:<p><b>JUST CAUSE: How to Win Disciplinary Grievances<br></b>Mon
 day\, May 24 at 7:30 p.m. EDT<br>We deserve nothing less than just cause\, 
 no exceptions.&nbsp\;This webinar is based on Robert M. Schwartz's book "Ju
 st Cause: A Union Guide to Winning Disciplinary Grievances." Among the subj
 ects covered are lax enforcement\, due process\, hearsay evidence\, dispara
 te treatment\, and progressive discipline.</p><p><a href="https://us02web.z
 oom.us/webinar/register/WN_rZuD_MuhRfG5knyyVLcXmg"><b>Please register for t
 his workshop&nbsp\;</b><b>here</b><b>.</b></a></p><p>To learn more\, check 
 out Robert M. Schwartz's&nbsp\;<a href="https://labornotes.org/store/books/
 work-rights-press">Work Rights Press</a>&nbsp\;book series:</p><ul> <li><a 
 href="https://labornotes.org/store/legal-rights-union-stewards">The Legal R
 ights of Union     Stewards</a></li> <li><a href="https://labornotes.org/st
 ore/just-cause">Just Cause: A Union Guide     to Winning Discipline Cases</
 a></li> <li><a href="https://labornotes.org/store/no-contract-no-peace">No 
 Contract\, No Peace: A     Legal Guide to Contract Campaigns\, Strikes\, an
 d Lockouts</a></li> <li><a href="https://labornotes.org/store/how-win-past-
 practice-grievances">How to Win Past Practice     Grievances</a></li> <li><
 a href="https://labornotes.org/store/fmla-handbook">The FMLA Handbook: A Un
 ion     Guide to the Family and Medical Leave Act</a></li> <li><a href="htt
 ps://labornotes.org/store/labor-law-source-book">The Labor Law Source Book:
      Full Texts of Federal Labor Laws</a></li></ul>
LAST-MODIFIED:20210429T190921Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:JUST CAUSE: How to Win Disciplinary Grievances 
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
