DTEND:20211026T000000Z
DTSTAMP:20260327T022744Z
UID:51ldj13oqbsdsnlgn5euqu2u97@google.com
CREATED:20210923T115121Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>Building To A Strike To Beat the Boss: How The New Yorker Un
 ion Won Their Contract<br></p><p>Last summer\, The New Yorker Union won a h
 istoric first contract at the magazine after they turned up the heat and pu
 t a credible strike threat on the table. Come hear from those workers about
  how they did it\, what they learned\, and how you can do the same in your 
 workplace.</p><p><a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSevDvv9F
 rWd4H-lOyi-9uQFyqJeb2XLAuBS2mVa-rG5YNXtRg/viewform?usp=sf_link">REGISTER HE
 RE</a></p><p>This is a repeat of the Oct. 7 panel.</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20210923T224752Z
SEQUENCE:4
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Building To A Strike To Beat the Boss: How The New Yorker Union Won
  Their Contract 
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260222T190000Z
DTEND:20260222T203000Z
DTSTAMP:20260327T022744Z
UID:4d7lh08vcrt1mflnp6n0o3ie2b@google.com
CREATED:20260220T152857Z
DESCRIPTION:<br>Join laid-off workers from Amazon\, Washington Post Tech\, 
 and other companies for a critical organizing call.<br><br><a href="https:/
 /wwwrise.org/">https://wwwrise.org/</a><br><br>Register here: <a href="http
 s://actionnetwork.org/forms/what-we-will/">https://actionnetwork.org/forms/
 what-we-will/</a><br><br>If you were recently laid off\, if you are current
 ly unemployed or anxious about future layoffs - or if you are a friend or f
 amily member standing in solidarity with laid-off workers - <strong>this ca
 ll is for you.</strong> It's time to build community\, share resources\, an
 d organize for the policy changes we urgently need.<br><br><br><h3>What We'
 ll Cover</h3><br><br><br><b>Know Your Rights</b><br>Guidance on post-layoff
  protections and navigating the system<br><br><br><b>Accessing Benefits</b>
 <br>How to file for unemployment insurance and other benefits<br><br><br><b
 >Mutual Aid</b><br>Supporting vulnerable workers — including H-1B visa hold
 ers and those facing healthcare gaps — and sharing job search resources<br>
 <br><br><b>Organizing for Change</b><br>Demand expanded unemployment insura
 nce\, public reskilling programs\, and a seat at the table in AI policy dec
 isions — at the federal\, state\, and local levels<br><h3>Speakers Include<
 /h3><br><br><br>Amazon Workers &amp\; Tech Workers Coalition<br>Helen<br><b
 r><br>Washington Post Tech Guild<br>Hazel<br><br><br>National Employment La
 w Project<br>Andrew Stettner<br><br><br>DSA Tech Action<br>Ajeet<br><br><br
 >WHAT WE WILL: Workers United for Just Transitions<br>Kaitlin<a href="https
 ://www.gofundme.com/f/washington-post-tech-guild-dont-take-the-bezos-bribe"
  target="_blank"><br></a>
LAST-MODIFIED:20260220T152857Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Mass Call: Laid-Off Tech Workers and Allies
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
