UID:55oqp6b6cs25eo1geflsfn60db@google.com
CREATED:20250113T161951Z
DESCRIPTION:Open to NewsGuild-CWA members only. <br><br>How do we effective
 ly help our coworkers? Being a steward is one great way to make a differenc
 e in your workplace. But what does it mean to be a steward? We will talk ab
 out the critical roles and responsibilities of union stewards while equippi
 ng participants with essential tools and strategies for success. Designed t
 o foster collaboration\, build skills\, and enhance understanding\, the ses
 sion emphasizes the importance of effective organizing\, communication\, an
 d problem-solving. <br><br>Key Learning Objectives: <br>- Understand the ro
 les and qualities of effective stewards. <br>- Explore the critical role of
  stewards as the heart of a union. <br>- Learn the structure and value of o
 rganizing conversations to build union power.<br><br>Register here: <a href
 ="https://us06web.zoom.us/meeting/register/tZYtf-CvpjsuG9GpT4FGc9vgAzDXJ3GZ
 SEjU#/registration">https://us06web.zoom.us/meeting/register/tZYtf-CvpjsuG9
 GpT4FGc9vgAzDXJ3GZSEjU#/registration</a>
LAST-MODIFIED:20250113T161951Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Training: Building Union Power and Effective Stewardship
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20210505T230000Z
DTEND:20210506T000000Z
DTSTAMP:20260327T022744Z
UID:38i5n1qv4qtbaa8d8nglnc3hsu@google.com
CREATED:20210429T133036Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>Join us!<br><br>The news and information that Chicago depend
 s on faces an uncertain future\, as a New York hedge fund bids to take over
  the Tribune Publishing\, parent company of the Chicago Tribune and newspap
 ers across the city and suburbs. Join the workers of Tribune newspapers acr
 oss the U.S.\, and stand up with us to fight for the news coverage our comm
 unities need — and deserve.</p><p>On May 5\, 6 p.m. CT\, the Save Local New
 s coalition of NewsGuild of Chicago Tribune Publishing Unions will host a f
 orum with community partners to:<br></p><ul><li>Create a vision for the fut
 ure of local news in Chicago and our state</li><li>Identify the challenges 
 to that vision\, and ways to overcome them</li><li>Plan for action to work 
 together to get the news our community needs<br></li></ul><p>Media workers 
 under Tribune unanimously want to cover local news important to the diverse
  communities of Chicago. Tribune Publishing management talks the talk\, but
  under hedge fund ownership\, simply does not walk the walk.</p><p>Newspape
 rs are under increasing pressures as an industry – and vultures like Alden 
 Global Capital are stripping resources from our papers and communities to l
 ine their pockets.<br>A better future is possible.</p><p>Register for the e
 vent here:&nbsp\;<a href="https://zoom.us/webinar/register/WN_PfwZp71iS3qza
 nuJym-blw">https://zoom.us/webinar/<wbr>register/WN_<wbr>PfwZp71iS3qzanuJym
 -blw</a></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20210429T133036Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Chicago Community Forum 
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20220515T150000Z
DTEND:20220515T163000Z
DTSTAMP:20260327T022744Z
UID:31u1hl8j2qeobhnfa50cmo2t8u@google.com
CREATED:20220419T195215Z
DESCRIPTION:<u></u><span><span><span>Take a few minutes to read through the
  <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://drive.google.com/file/d/1Di4
 BYtPiATTJCni7bKvJ1OmeTd3YhqBq/view?usp%3Dsharing&amp\;sa=D&amp\;source=cale
 ndar&amp\;ust=1650829902756523&amp\;usg=AOvVaw1ag0qPjW3fAEzOzTRmjmnJ" targe
 t="_blank">Law360          case study!</a><br> <br><u>Goals we&#39\;ll focu
 s on during our workshop:</u><br>            <ul><li>Assess     structure a
 nd communication within our units and plan to achieve specific     goals to
 ward high function.</li><li>Assess     power: who is their target\, what wi
 ll it take to move the target\, where is     their leverage</li><li>Build  
    your team</li><li>Make     plan for identifying and/or review demands</l
 i><li>Plot     contract timeline (dates set and to be determined)</li><li>P
 lot     on to timeline: meetings with members\, escalating actions going af
 ter     target\, reaching out to labor and community for support.</li></ul>
 </span></span></span>  <br><u></u><br><u></u>Register in advance for this m
 eeting:<br><a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://zoom.us/meeting/re
 gister/tJYrd--urDIrG9f7bS2AdSa_99HSf8Q7TaJH&amp\;sa=D&amp\;source=calendar&
 amp\;ust=1650829902756523&amp\;usg=AOvVaw32SNKG0s8Khxk_NPFd-MKo" target="_b
 lank">https://zoom.us/meeting/register/tJYrd--urDIrG9f7bS2AdSa_99HSf8Q7TaJH
 </a><u></u>
