UID:0fp8tmjse7863ca8n505jhanb6@google.com
CREATED:20211103T214437Z
DESCRIPTION:Running effective meetings is a key part of building a strong u
 nion! But do your union meetings drag on too long? Does it feel like the sa
 me people are always talking? Is not enough getting done? Are the meetings 
 just plain boring? Well\, you are not alone! In this workshop we will discu
 ss how to run effective meetings. Learn how to create a strong agenda\, sta
 y on task\, get real work done\, and make the experience enjoyable in the p
 rocess!<br><br>Offered by The NewsGuild of New York.&nbsp\;<br>7-8 p.m. ET\
 , Nov. 18\, 2021<br>This training will be repeated Nov. 30.<br><br>Register
  <a href="https://nyguild.us15.list-manage.com/track/click?u=424ca69b0f8815
 861592760f3&id=0175dbde76&e=bf01c8ef11">here</a>.
LAST-MODIFIED:20211104T154746Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Effective Meeting Facilitation
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20220629T220000Z
DTEND:20220630T003000Z
DTSTAMP:20260327T022744Z
UID:7tfn3v5u7hq3t5vtvgdeij936q@google.com
CREATED:20220411T224350Z
DESCRIPTION:<h2><b><a href="https://www.nyguild.org/event-details/labor-law
 -101-1378" id="ow3897" __is_owner="true">Labor Law 101</a></b></h2><br><p><
 strong><b>When:&nbsp\;</b></strong><time>06/29/2022\, 6 pm – 8:30 pm ET</ti
 me></p><p><strong><b>Where:&nbsp\;</b></strong>On Zoom</p><p>Every union me
 mber should know the basics of labor law and how to use it. This training p
 rovides activists with an introduction to labor law—the rights provided to 
 workers\, how those rights are enforced\, and how to spot some of the ways 
 that employers will bend and break the law to try and undermine our collect
 ive power.</p><p>This workshop is facilitated by Gay Semel\, retired attorn
 ey who previously worked at Region 2 of the NLRB and was District Counsel f
 or District 1 of CWA for more than 30 years.&nbsp\;</p><p><strong><b><a hre
 f="https://forms.gle/uheGd1qF9ukQSrBh6"><b>REGISTER HERE</b></a></b></stron
 g></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20220411T224350Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Labor Law 101
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20210519T160000Z
DTEND:20210519T180000Z
DTSTAMP:20260327T022744Z
UID:2o6ssa850iv9jcll5jbl646r81@google.com
CREATED:20210516T111915Z
DESCRIPTION:<br><br><br><b>Wednesday 19 May\, 17:00&nbsp\;(UK) Journalism u
 nder attack: unions fight back!&nbsp\;</b><p>From killings to jailings\, fr
 om internet shutdowns to job cuts and media closures\, journalism across th
 e globe is under threat.&nbsp\;Join the International Federation of Journal
 ists and unions from around the world to hear about how unions are fighting
  back - and what you can do to stand in solidarity. Jeremy Dear\, IFJ deput
 y general secretary\, will chair a panel of speakers including:&nbsp\;</p><
 br><ul><li><b>Nasser Abu Bakr\, President of the Palestinian Journalists Sy
 ndicate</b>&nbsp\;on the current military offensive in Gaza and the targeti
 ng of journalists</li><li><b>Sakeus Likela\,&nbsp\;general secretary of the
