DESCRIPTION:“No Such Thing as a Union Boss\,” is a panel discussion about t
 ropes and trip-ups in labor reporting\, featuring Maximillian Alvarez\, Bra
 den Campbell\, Sarah Jaffe\, and Kim Kelly. The panel will take place on Zo
 om\, on Tuesday\, June 20\, at 12pm ET. The National Writers Union/Freelanc
 e Solidarity Project\, WGAE\, and The NewsGuild are co-hosting.<br><br>Stri
 kes are everywhere in the news right now. So why is so much media coverage 
 of strikes still so bad? As both professional storytellers and unionized wo
 rkers themselves\, these seasoned labor journalists understand the power of
  public narrative to support or undermine workers’ movements—and the way pe
 rvasive anti-union sentiment distorts coverage of labor issues. In this pan
 el\, they’ll shed light on common failures of uninformed and anti-worker la
 bor reporting\, and discuss how the precarious labor conditions of the medi
 a industry impact the quality of coverage.<br><br>Please RSVP in order to r
 eceive a link to join the online panel: <a href="http://freelancesolidarity
 .org/labor-reporting">freelancesolidarity.org/labor-<wbr />reporting</a>
LAST-MODIFIED:20250329T014212Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Panel: No Such Things as a Union Boss... and other things the media
  gets wrong about labor
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
