DESCRIPTION:Every union member should know the basics of labor law and how 
 to use it. This training provides activists with an introduction to labor l
 aw—the rights provided to workers\, how those rights are enforced\, and how
  to spot some of the ways that employers will bend and break the law to try
  and undermine our collective power.<p>This workshop is facilitated by Gay 
 Semel\, retired attorney who previously worked at Region 2 of the NLRB and 
 was District Counsel for District 1 of CWA for more than 30 years.&nbsp\;</
 p><p><a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdKy-UOOWyos8uleWMM1
 pu5RgdLttYyb4TRJPf-mEhI9wQdsA/viewform?usp=sf_link">REGISTER HERE</a></p><p
 >This is a repeat of the Oct. 2 workshop.</p>
