DESCRIPTION:<p>Every union member should know the basics of labor law and h
 ow to use it. This training provides activists with an introduction to labo
 r law—the rights provided to workers\, how those rights are enforced\, and 
 how to spot some of the ways that employers will bend and break the law to 
 try and undermine our collective power.</p><p>This workshop is facilitated 
 by Gay Semel\, retired attorney who previously worked at Region 2 of the NL
 RB and was District Counsel for District 1 of CWA for more than 30 years.&n
 bsp\;</p><p><strong><b><a href="https://forms.gle/uheGd1qF9ukQSrBh6" id="ow
 11020" __is_owner="true"><b>REGISTER HERE</b></a></b></strong></p>
