BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20220616T000000Z
DTEND:20220616T013000Z
DTSTAMP:20260327T022744Z
UID:7vbq925lkn91pcme43f6g3cqlr@google.com
CREATED:20220602T143616Z
DESCRIPTION:<p><a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdGBZmC9N7
 U4SIO8QeesR8H8gVe0Nq5IZRBoVK6jM2ICSkSzw/viewform" id="ow2971" __is_owner="t
 rue">Register here.</a></p><p>Corporations have been quick to claim support
  for diversity\, equity and inclusion but slow to implement meaningful chan
 ge in their workplaces. Meanwhile\, workers have become disillusioned by br
 oken promises of corporate accountability and transparency.</p><p>News medi
 a companies are part of the problem. They’re willing to spend big money on 
 diversity consulting firms but refuse to invest in pay equity\, hiring and 
 retention\, or to acknowledge and dismantle racist structures in their news
 rooms. As organized media workers\, we have an opportunity to hold our empl
 oyers — and ourselves — accountable.</p><p>NewsGuild members are invited an
 d encouraged to participate in an assembly at 8 p.m. ET Wednesday\, June 15
 .</p><p><a href="https://click.actionnetwork.org/ss/c/SVVf6UGddUySPN6znLYVW
 uLeaebjGRu1gg_sZyCVV3puv4ehKLrQvbo04IjQTkyuwXAbHpMEsaAd67n6QK3-KTKe9UBQaFYL
 2TDu0ZDjhQbFg2pE25ZqR8GF5wvRbG2LyCTGtFzF4RJy9snelPTBjKPVAT3AuP1iy4oAa13hJUs
 Ybq-7xoqYuOlsIsbBzTvTBRg8RtE-SIEcjEkXNjRc0PTgaexKxGTfjRNUv9q8zIR7Qxw3xDpnWy
 46fNwR_9suxDBfhLrGSCbWMuw3_eRuzsHaFSvsFMaMv0N76fuPTvM/3mk/Fx2Cmzw_TzGPO6gGJ
 JJlUw/h0/POLscDG8GXlnzbFUSZGXy1kAnJ-LI_PIi2ClAjw5AIc"><strong>Was that the 
 Reckoning? Addressing anti-Black racism in the news industry</strong></a></
 p><p>Attendees will hear from Pulitzer Prize-winning journalist Nikole Hann
 ah-Jones\, as well as Susan DeCarava\, president of The NewsGuild of New Yo
 rk\, and Desiree Stennett\, race and equity reporter at the Orlando Sentine
 l.</p><p>The keynote and panel will be followed by breakout rooms where we 
 will collectively identify next steps to organize against anti-Blackness an
 d fight for an anti-racist future in our union and in the news media indust
 ry.</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20220602T143750Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Was That the Reckoning? Addressing Anti-Black Racism in the News In
 dustry
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
