UID:0hbrak0e8momanr5bpflj9g5it@google.com
CREATED:20210405T140821Z
DESCRIPTION:<p><b>Due to unforeseen circumstances\, tonight's webinar has b
 een postponed. We regret the inconvenience.</b></p><p><b>PAST PRACTICES: WH
 AT ARE THEY AND WHEN ARE THEY BINDING<br></b>Monday\, June 28 at 7:30 p.m. 
 EDT</p><p>Stewards need to know what a valid past practice is and what the 
 past practices in their workplace are in order to defend them from erosion 
 by management. This webinar will cover how unions can build power on the jo
 b through past practice grievances.</p><p><a href="https://us02web.zoom.us/
 webinar/register/WN_23vkFHhCQzmSCV1TU3SXdg"><b>Please register for this wor
 kshop&nbsp\;</b><b>here</b><b>.</b></a></p><p>To learn more\, check out Rob
 ert M. Schwartz's&nbsp\;<a href="https://labornotes.org/store/books/work-ri
 ghts-press">Work Rights Press</a>&nbsp\;bookseries:</p><p></p><ul> <li><a h
 ref="https://labornotes.org/store/legal-rights-union-stewards">The Legal Ri
 ghts of Union     Stewards</a></li> <li><a href="https://labornotes.org/sto
 re/just-cause">Just Cause: A Union Guide to     Winning Discipline Cases</a
 ></li> <li><a href="https://labornotes.org/store/no-contract-no-peace">No C
 ontract\, No Peace: A Legal     Guide to Contract Campaigns\, Strikes\, and
  Lockouts</a></li> <li><a href="https://labornotes.org/store/how-win-past-p
 ractice-grievances">How to Win Past Practice     Grievances</a></li> <li><a
  href="https://labornotes.org/store/fmla-handbook">The FMLA Handbook: A Uni
 on     Guide to the Family and Medical Leave Act</a></li> <li><a href="http
 s://labornotes.org/store/labor-law-source-book">The Labor Law Source Book: 
     Full Texts of Federal Labor Laws</a>&nbsp\;</li></ul>
LAST-MODIFIED:20220618T103254Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:POSTPONED: Past Practices: What are they and when are they binding?
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20240807T230000Z
DTEND:20240808T003000Z
DTSTAMP:20260327T022744Z
UID:73tq9e9rag6gi39lee19sem0u8@google.com
CREATED:20240725T225608Z
DESCRIPTION:<h3>This workshop has limited capacity and is for stewards and 
 elected officers who work with stewards - not staff. Please register only i
 f this applies to you.</h3><p><b>When: Wednesday\, Aug. 7<br>Time: 7:00 p.m
 . to 8:30 p.m. Eastern (4.00 p.m. to 5:30 p.m. Pacific).<br>Where: This is 
 an online workshop and will be held via Zoom.</b> </p><p>Leadership isn’t a
 bout taking everything on ourselves—it’s about developing others to partici
 pate\, by providing the resources and opportunity. </p><p>Using the <a href
 ="https://www.labornotes.org/2022/04/learn-it-do-it-teach-it-member-organiz
 ers-turn-moment-movement">“Learn It\, Do It\, Teach It”</a> philosophy\, th
 is workshop will cover how to get more people involved and expand the capac
 ity of your union.</p><p>This workshop will be run by organizers from the N
 ewsGuild-CWA.</p><p>Registration is $10 - no one will be turned away for la
 ck of funds. Reach out if you need the registration fee waived.</p><p><stro
 ng>If you have problems signing up\, or can't find a Zoom link after regist
 ering\, please email our Communications Organizer Sindhu Sundar at <a href=
 "mailto:sindhu@labornotes.org">sindhu@labornotes.org</a>.</strong></p><p>To
  register: <a href="https://labornotes.org/events/2024/stewards-workshop-yo
 u-cant-do-it-all-yourself-learn-it-do-it-teach-it-august-2024">https://labo
 rnotes.org/events/2024/stewards-workshop-you-cant-do-it-all-yourself-learn-
 it-do-it-teach-it-august-2024</a></p><p>If you want to register more than o
 ne person\, change the quantity of registrations in your shopping cart on t
 he next page.</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20240725T225608Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Labor Notes Stewards' Workshop: You Can't Do It All Yourself: Learn
  it\, Do it\, Teach it
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
