DESCRIPTION:<br><br><p>Register: <a href="https://zoom.us/meeting/register/
 tJwqf-GtrjwvHdwnSVlC4DwYmQY9pVGMd-5o">https://zoom.us/meeting/register/tJwq
 f-GtrjwvHdwnSVlC4DwYmQY9pVGMd-5o</a>&nbsp\;</p><p><br></p><ol><li><p>The St
 ructure of an Organizing Conversation (15 min) - Natalia</p></li></ol><ol><
 li><p><a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1E3kQuGCJ7uD8f_z_mKecN_PO
 KO-_zH6jIxUSaDxJ3L4/edit?usp=drive_web&ouid=110043571617242606019">A.E.I.O.
 U. for Union Shops &amp\; Tips for One-on-Ones</a></p></li><li><p>Read thro
 ugh each part of the conversation\, come up with examples for each part</p>
 </li></ol><p>B. Semantics - how we talk about our union (10 min) - Priscill
 a</p><ol><li><p>Words matter! We don’t use apologetic language like thank y
 ou or sorry.</p></li><li><p>Talk about your union with confidence and excit
 ement! Not as if it’s a burden.</p></li><li><p><a href="https://docs.google
 .com/document/d/1O0ifAidnXRxDCeZi0RLutNZR2yEayKdSljvrEdWzvLA/edit">Semantic
 s Exercise for Stewards</a></p></li></ol><p>C. Answering Tough Questions - 
 Affirm\, Answer\, Redirect (10 min) - Natalia</p><ol><li><p><a href="https:
 //drive.google.com/file/d/194-onBpLtFjnqPp-HTWN_U_jwgI2jzy6/view?usp=sharin
 g">Practice Answering Tough Questions</a> - fill out on your own\, a few pe
 ople share back</p></li></ol><p>D. Role Plays (25 min) - Stephanie</p><ol><
 li><p>Facilitator model a conversation</p></li><li><p>Breakout rooms to pra
 ctice in pairs (20 min)</p></li></ol><br>Agenda:<br><a href="https://docs.g
 oogle.com/document/d/1VpMDzpcGlQ1qukpldt9GvS6-SZMgNmPy8DeN8cUSfBM/edit">htt
 ps://docs.google.com/document/d/1VpMDzpcGlQ1qukpldt9GvS6-SZMgNmPy8DeN8cUSfB
 M/edit</a><br><br><ol><br></ol>
