DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><table><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td><table><
 tbody><tr><td>In perhaps&nbsp\;one of the most&nbsp\;challenging moments in
  a generation\, workers are leading&nbsp\;inspiring\, incredible&nbsp\;orga
 nizing&nbsp\;by taking on large\, private employers.&nbsp\;These workers ar
 e fighting for not just themselves\, but their communities and a better\, m
 ore just world.&nbsp\;<br><br>Drawing on this energy\, the Bargaining for t
 he Common Good network is convening activists from&nbsp\;across the labor m
 ovement to<b>&nbsp\;</b>strategize and&nbsp\;build on this moment.&nbsp\;Jo
 in a<i style="">&nbsp\;</i>strategy session to dig in on common good organi
 zing and bargaining in the private sector with activists including:<ul><li>
 Leaders from unions and community organizations like janitors and students 
 in Minnesota organizing for climate justice</li><li><b>Reporters across the
  nation fighting to save local news</b></li><li>Healthcare workers in Conne
 cticut taking on racial injustice</li><li>Telecom technicians organizing wi
 th their communities to win broadband for all&nbsp\;</li></ul>These movemen
 t leaders demonstrate how common good strategies can build power in the pri
 vate sector and will share their stories and recommendations based on their
  experiences. We warmly welcome&nbsp\;organizations that are new to BCG and
  curious about how it could be put to use in their context.</td></tr></tbod
 y></table></td></tr></tbody></table><table><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr
 ><td></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table><table><tbody><tr>
 <td><table><tbody><tr><td><i><a href="https://georgetown.us2.list-manage.co
 m/track/click?u=5ee1c8d02c777988a335b892f&id=07378af3de&e=63b043457a"><u>Re
 gister</u></a>&nbsp\;to receive the full schedule and updates on the event.
  Please make requests for accommodation to&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:kilwp@geor
 getown.edu">kilwp@georgetown.edu</a>&nbsp\;by June 22\, a good faith effort
  will be made to fulfill requests made after that date.&nbsp\;</i></td></tr
 ></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table><table><tbody><tr><td><table><tb
 ody><tr><td></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><
 tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td><a href="https://georget
 own.us2.list-manage.com/track/click?u=5ee1c8d02c777988a335b892f&id=077a4d8c
